Stateful Snapshot for Splunk empowers Splunk administrators to capture Splunk's point-in-time state (such as configuration files and KVStore). These "snapshots" are automatically (configurable) generated and retained for a configurable period of time or up to a total disk usage.
For more information such as instructions, prerequisites, and more please visit Stateful Snapshot for Splunk on Splunkbase (https://splunkbase.splunk.com/app/4122/)